          "question": {
            "en": {
              "comprehension": null,
              "direction": null,
              "content": "<p>Let $$f(x)=\\frac{x}{\\left(1+x^{n}\\right)^{1 / n}}$$ for $$n \\geq 2$$ and $$g(x)=\\underbrace{(f o f o \\ldots . o f)}_{f \\text { occurs } n \\text { times }}(x)$$. Then $$\\int x^{n-2} g(x) d x$$ equals :</p>",
              "options": [
                {
                  "identifier": "A",
                  "content": "$$\\frac{1}{n(n-1)}\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{1-\\frac{1}{n}}+k$$"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "B",
                  "content": "$$\\frac{1}{n(n+1)}\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{1-\\frac{1}{n}}+k$$"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "C",
                  "content": "$$\\frac{1}{n(n-1)}\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{1-\\frac{1}{n}}+k$$"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "D",
                  "content": "$$\\frac{1}{(n+1)}\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{1+\\frac{1}{n}}+k$$"
                }
              ],
              "correct_options": [
                "A"
              ],
              "answer": null,
              "explanation": "<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { Given, } f(x)=\\frac{x}{\\left(1+x^{n}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{n}}} \\\\\n& \\therefore f(f(x))=\\frac{y}{\\left(1+y^{n}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{n}}} \\text {, where } y=\\frac{x}{\\left(1+x^{n}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{n}}} \\\\\n& =\\frac{x}{\\left(1+2 x^{n}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{n}}}\n~~......(\\mathrm{i})\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>Similarly, $$f(f(f(x)))=\\frac{x}{\\left(1+3 x^{n}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{n}}}$$ and</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\frac{(f \\circ f \\circ f \\circ \\ldots f)(x)}{n \\text { times }} & =g(x)=\\frac{x}{\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{n}}}~~......(\\mathrm{ii}) \\\\\n\\int x^{n-2} g(x) d x & =\\int \\frac{x^{n-1}}{\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{1 / n}} d x \\\\\n& =\\frac{1}{n^{2}} \\int n^{2}\\left[x^{n-1}\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{\\frac{-1}{n}}\\right] d x \\\\\n& =\\frac{1}{n^{2}} \\cdot \\frac{\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{1-\\frac{1}{n}}}{1-\\frac{1}{n}}+k \\\\\n& =\\frac{\\left(1+n x^{n}\\right)^{1-\\frac{1}{n}}}{n(n-1)}+k\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>"
            }
          },
